headline: Visa, Mastercard, AmEx earnings: Trump's cap idea 'won't stick'
summary: Credit card companies, like Visa (V), Mastercard (MA), and American Express (AXP), are reporting quarterly earnings results this week.The earnings reports come as President Trump proposes a 10% cap on credit card interest rates. JPMorgan (JPM) CEO Jamie Dimon said this policy would create an "economic disaster."B. Riley Wealth chief market strategist, Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Brooke DiPalma, and Yahoo Finance Senior Business Reporter Ines Ferré join Opening Bid host Brian Sozzi to discuss their expectations.To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.

content.title: Visa, Mastercard, AmEx earnings: Trump's cap idea 'won't stick'
content.description:
Credit card companies, like Visa (V), Mastercard (MA), and American Express (AXP), are reporting quarterly earnings results this week.

headline: J.P. Morgan Asset Management Canada Launches International Developed Equity Active ETF
summary: J.P. Morgan Asset Management Canada (JPMAM) today announced the launch of the JPMorgan International Developed Equity Active ETF (TSX: JIDE), marking the firm's expansion into international developed equities as part of its growing Canadian ETF suite. headline: Trump Lawsuit Tests JPMorgan Governance Reputation And Long Term Investor Views
summary: Former President Donald Trump has filed a lawsuit against JPMorgan Chase and CEO Jamie Dimon, alleging that his accounts were closed for political reasons. The case brings fresh attention to so called debanking and to how large banks handle politically exposed clients. headline: Pharma Stocks Are Close to ‘Breaking Out.’ Earnings Could Set Them Free.
summary: Pharmaceutical stocks just broke out to new highs—and earnings could push them even higher.  The  exchange-traded fund is up 32% in the past six months to almost $57.  Also helping the rally is that healthcare companies are investing in artificial intelligence to help them identify revenue opportunities with lower costs, potentially lifting profit margins.
